    <p>
      The meteorological definition of autumn according to SMHI is:
      "that the daily average temperature shall be decreasing and lower than 10.0 plus degrees but higher than 0.0 °
      for five consecutive days". An additional condition is that autumn cannot begin before the 1st of August.
    </p>
    <p>
      This never happens in the data we have been assigned,
      therefore we have modified the conditions a bit and set them to falling and lower than 12 plus degrees.
      This is easily changed in the variables fallMin and fallMax.
    </p>
